gov.ca.water.calgui.bus_service.impl

Class DSSGrabber2SvcImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.ca.water.calgui.bus_service.impl.DSSGrabber1SvcImpl
      • gov.ca.water.calgui.bus_service.impl.DSSGrabber2SvcImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDSSGrabber1Svc

    public class DSSGrabber2SvcImpl
extends DSSGrabber1SvcImpl
    Class to grab (generate) DSS time series BASED ON DTS list for a set of scenarios passed in a JList. Each scenario is a string that corresponds to a fully qualified (?) DSS file name. The DSS_Grabber instance provides access to the following:
    • Main time series (result, including necessary math) for each scenario
    • Secondary series (control) where indicated for each scenario
    • Difference for main time series for each scenario
    • Exceedance for main time series for each scenario
    Typical usage sequence:
    • DSS_Grabber
    • setIsCFS
    • setBase
    • setLocation
    • setDateRange
    • getPrimarySeries
    • getSecondarySeries
    • Other calculations

      • setLocation

        public void setLocation(java.lang.String locationName)
        Sets dataset (DSS) names to read from scenario DSS files, title, and axis labels according to location specified using a coded string. The string is currently used as a lookup into either Schematic_DSS_Links4.table (if it starts with Constant.SCHEMATIC_PREFIX) or into GUI_Links3.table. These tables may be combined in Phase 2.
        Specified by:
